
---

## How to Run the Project
1. Upload dataset to Google Colab
2. Open the notebook
3. Run cells sequentially
4. Evaluate model results
5. (Optional) Deploy using Streamlit

---

## Results & Insights
- The model successfully captures volatility trends
- Rolling volatility and technical indicators significantly improve prediction accuracy
- Random Forest performs well for nonlinear financial data

---

## Conclusion
This project demonstrates how machine learning can be applied to **financial time-series data** to predict cryptocurrency volatility.  
It provides a solid foundation for further enhancements such as deep learning or real-time prediction systems.

